Baboon limbs were found hanging from the wall of a home in Boston, Bellville, allegedly to protect it from intruders, the Cape of Good Hope SPCA said yesterday.Inspectors responded to a tip-off and found two baboon hands and a severed foot dangling from a property&rsquo;s perimeter wall, the Cape of Good Hope Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals (SPCA) said in a statement.The SPCA said the occupants said they removed the limbs from a dead baboon they found on a farm. They would not disclose the location of the farm or the baboon's remains.&nbsp;&ldquo;Targeted for marauding and already treated with cruel intolerance [baboons] now face the additional threat of death and mutilation in the name of human protection,&rdquo; the statement reads.The limbs were confiscated to try and identify the farm in question. The SPCA was working with police and Cape Nature in the investigation.&ldquo;We will not hesitate to prosecute if proof of cruelty is found,&rdquo; it said.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/baboon-hands-found-dangling-from-cape-homes-wall-20170325